The Filecoin Foundation for the Decentralized Web is a nonprofit organization committed to preserving humanity’s most important information by fostering the development of open source software and open protocols.

The Filecoin Foundation (FF) is an independent
organization that facilitates governance of the
projects, supports the growth of the Filecoin
ecosystem, and advocates for Filecoin and the
decentralized web. FF does this by coordinating
and supporting the creation and improvement of
open-source software and open protocols for
decentralized data storage and retrieval networks.
The Filecoin Foundation for the Decentralized Web
(FFDW) focuses on charitable activities related to
preserving important datasets, such as building
and supporting the decentralized web community,
funding research and development, and educating
the public about the decentralized web.
